dataSetInformation.common:generalComment: Since 1995, the "European Database for Corrugated Board Life Cycle Studies" is part of an environmental project undertaken by FEFCO (F,d,ration Europ,enne des Fabricants de Carton Ondul,), GO (Groupement Europ,en des Fabricants de Papiers pour Ondul,) and ECO (European Containerboard Organisation). The data are collected and processed by the industry and are available from the industry itself in the form of this report. It is updated at least every 3 years, the last time in 2003. The data in this fifth edition represent the weighted averages of the inputs into and outputs from the production sites per ton net saleable product (paper and corrugated board) from the production sites for the year 2002. Additives that contribute less than 0,5 % of the weight of the net saleable product have not been updated. For these additives the data for 1999 are reported.

locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction.descriptionOfRestrictions: Average data for corrugated board box production, including printing, in EU-25 and Switzerland.

technology.technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesse: The corrugated board box for this purpose is composed of Kraftliner 19,3%, Testliner 43,8%, SC fluting 5,2%, recycled fluting 31,7%. The data represent average technology. They do not represent a certain mill with a certain technology, but a non-existent "mill" utilising different technologies. It contains data on the production of corrugated base papers from primary fibres: Semichemical Fluting and Kraftliner (data from European Containerboard Organisation), of the production of corrugated base papers from recovered papers: Testliner and Wellenstoff (data from Groupement Ondul√©) and of the production of corrugated board sheets and boxes (data from FEFCO).
technology.technologicalApplicability: Corrugated board is a high performance packaging material designed to pack, protect and promote products.

LCIMethodAndAllocation.deviationsFromLCIMethodApproaches: For details, please see "European Database for Corrugated Board Life Cycle Studies" (Report)
LCIMethodAndAllocation.modellingConstants: All data used in the calculation of the LCI results refer to net calorific value.

dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativenes.dataCutOffAndCompletenessPrinciples: The "European Database for Corrugated Board Life Cycle Studies" covers >99% of the relevant mass, energy and measured output flows from the unit process flows and >95% including background system.
dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativenes.dataSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples: The data sources for the complete product system are sufficiently consistent. The input flows and output flows from the production sites are based on measured operating data. Secondary data are European average data from the GaBi databases 2006. LCI modelling is fully consistent.
dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativenes.dataTreatmentAndExtrapolationsPrinciples: The data sets in the "European Database for corrugated board Life Cycle Studies" contains data sets that are calculated as weighted average from production sites. If data were lacking from a certain location for a certain flow, then the location was not inlcuded in the calculations for that flow. UCTE power grid mix was taken into account. An UCTE equivalent steam profile was used (based on share and representative steam production in the different countries). All upstream chemicals represent either European or central European average.
dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativenes.useAdviceForDataSet: The data set may only be used for environmental studies regarding product development and improvement and the comparison of the entire system of corrugated board packaging with that of other materials. The data set may not be used for comparisons between the production of primary fibre and recovered fibre based materials as such, nor for benchmarking between countries. Corrugated board boxes are far from standardised. They show a huge variation in composition, design and appearance. Boxes are tailor made to fit the box users need and requirements set by the product to be packed. For detailed studies for specific boxes it is highly recommended to get in touch with FEFCO: information@fefco.org

review.common:otherReviewDetails: The data set is of adequate data quality in view of the use as well as stated time, geography, and technology coverage.

publicationAndOwnership.common:accessRestrictions: The data set can be used free of charge by anybody to perform LCA studies, to distribute it to third parties, to convert it to other formats, to develop own data sets etc. as long as the copyright and license conditions for the ELCD data sets and the ILCD format are met that can be accessed via http://lca.jrc.ec.europa.eu. Please note e.g. that reference must be given to the 'Owner of data set' and to the 'ELCD database' plus version number, when using the data set or parts thereof. Please note also, that any modifications/omissions of the data set results in invalidity of any existing 'Official approval of data set by producer/operator', that the impression must be avoided that this would still be a complete ELCD data set, and that the content of further fields has to be adjusted. For details see the aforementioned copyright and license conditions.
